30size_t GetMaximumMipLevel(const gl::Context *context, gl::TextureType type)
31{
32 const gl::Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
33
34 int maxDimension = 0;
35 switch (type)
36 {
37 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
38 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
39 case gl::TextureType::_2DMultisample:
40 maxDimension = caps.max2DTextureSize;
41 break;
42 case gl::TextureType::Rectangle:
43 maxDimension = caps.maxRectangleTextureSize;
44 break;
45 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
46 maxDimension = caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize;
47 break;
48 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
49 maxDimension = caps.max3DTextureSize;
50 break;
51
52 default:
53 UNREACHABLE();
54 }
55
56 return gl::log2(maxDimension);
57}
58
59bool TextureHasNonZeroMipLevelsSpecified(const gl::Context *context, const gl::Texture *texture)
60{
61 size_t maxMip = GetMaximumMipLevel(context, texture->getType());
62 for (size_t level = 1; level < maxMip; level++)
63 {
64 if (texture->getType() == gl::TextureType::CubeMap)
65 {
66 for (gl::TextureTarget face : gl::AllCubeFaceTextureTargets())
67 {
68 if (texture->getFormat(face, level).valid())
69 {
70 return true;
71 }
72 }
73 }
74 else
75 {
76 if (texture->getFormat(gl::NonCubeTextureTypeToTarget(texture->getType()), level)
77 .valid())
78 {
79 return true;
80 }
81 }
82 }
83
84 return false;
85}
86
87bool CubeTextureHasUnspecifiedLevel0Face(const gl::Texture *texture)
88{
89 ASSERT(texture->getType() == gl::TextureType::CubeMap);
90 for (gl::TextureTarget face : gl::AllCubeFaceTextureTargets())
91 {
92 if (!texture->getFormat(face, 0).valid())
93 {
94 return true;
95 }
96 }
97
98 return false;
99}

101Error ValidateStreamAttribute(const EGLAttrib attribute,
102 const EGLAttrib value,
103 const DisplayExtensions &extensions)
104{
105 switch (attribute)
106 {
107 case EGL_STREAM_STATE_KHR:
108 case EGL_PRODUCER_FRAME_KHR:
109 case EGL_CONSUMER_FRAME_KHR:
110 return EglBadAccess() << "Attempt to initialize readonly parameter";
111 case EGL_CONSUMER_LATENCY_USEC_KHR:
112 // Technically not in spec but a latency < 0 makes no sense so we check it
113 if (value < 0)
114 {
115 return EglBadParameter() << "Latency must be positive";
116 }
117 break;
118 case EGL_CONSUMER_ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT_USEC_KHR:
119 if (!extensions.streamConsumerGLTexture)
120 {
121 return EglBadAttribute() << "Consumer GL extension not enabled";
122 }
123 // Again not in spec but it should be positive anyways
124 if (value < 0)
125 {
126 return EglBadParameter() << "Timeout must be positive";
127 }
128 break;
129 default:
130 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid stream attribute";
131 }
132 return NoError();
133}
134
135Error ValidateCreateImageMipLevelCommon(gl::Context *context,
136 const gl::Texture *texture,
137 EGLAttrib level)
138{
139 // Note that the spec EGL_create_image spec does not explicitly specify an error
140 // when the level is outside the base/max level range, but it does mention that the
141 // level "must be a part of the complete texture object <buffer>". It can be argued
142 // that out-of-range levels are not a part of the complete texture.
143 const GLuint effectiveBaseLevel = texture->getTextureState().getEffectiveBaseLevel();
144 if (level > 0 &&
145 (!texture->isMipmapComplete() || static_cast<GLuint>(level) < effectiveBaseLevel ||
146 static_cast<GLuint>(level) > texture->getTextureState().getMipmapMaxLevel()))
147 {
148 return EglBadParameter() << "texture must be complete if level is non-zero.";
149 }
150
151 if (level == 0 && !texture->isMipmapComplete() &&
152 TextureHasNonZeroMipLevelsSpecified(context, texture))
153 {
154 return EglBadParameter() << "if level is zero and the texture is incomplete, it must "
155 "have no mip levels specified except zero.";
156 }
157
158 return NoError();
159}

161Error ValidateConfigAttribute(const Display *display, EGLAttrib attribute)
162{
163 switch (attribute)
164 {
165 case EGL_BUFFER_SIZE:
166 case EGL_ALPHA_SIZE:
167 case EGL_BLUE_SIZE:
168 case EGL_GREEN_SIZE:
169 case EGL_RED_SIZE:
170 case EGL_DEPTH_SIZE:
171 case EGL_STENCIL_SIZE:
172 case EGL_CONFIG_CAVEAT:
173 case EGL_CONFIG_ID:
174 case EGL_LEVEL:
175 case EGL_NATIVE_RENDERABLE:
176 case EGL_NATIVE_VISUAL_ID:
177 case EGL_NATIVE_VISUAL_TYPE:
178 case EGL_SAMPLES:
179 case EGL_SAMPLE_BUFFERS:
180 case EGL_SURFACE_TYPE:
181 case EGL_TRANSPARENT_TYPE:
182 case EGL_TRANSPARENT_BLUE_VALUE:
183 case EGL_TRANSPARENT_GREEN_VALUE:
184 case EGL_TRANSPARENT_RED_VALUE:
185 case EGL_BIND_TO_TEXTURE_RGB:
186 case EGL_BIND_TO_TEXTURE_RGBA:
187 case EGL_MIN_SWAP_INTERVAL:
188 case EGL_MAX_SWAP_INTERVAL:
189 case EGL_LUMINANCE_SIZE:
190 case EGL_ALPHA_MASK_SIZE:
191 case EGL_COLOR_BUFFER_TYPE:
192 case EGL_RENDERABLE_TYPE:
193 case EGL_MATCH_NATIVE_PIXMAP:
194 case EGL_CONFORMANT:
195 case EGL_MAX_PBUFFER_WIDTH:
196 case EGL_MAX_PBUFFER_HEIGHT:
197 case EGL_MAX_PBUFFER_PIXELS:
198 break;
199
200 case EGL_OPTIMAL_SURFACE_ORIENTATION_ANGLE:
201 if (!display->getExtensions().surfaceOrientation)
202 {
203 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_surface_orientation is not enabled.";
204 }
205 break;
206
207 case EGL_COLOR_COMPONENT_TYPE_EXT:
208 if (!display->getExtensions().pixelFormatFloat)
209 {
210 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_EXT_pixel_format_float is not enabled.";
211 }
212 break;
213
214 case EGL_RECORDABLE_ANDROID:
215 if (!display->getExtensions().recordable)
216 {
217 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANDROID_recordable is not enabled.";
218 }
219 break;
220
221 case EGL_FRAMEBUFFER_TARGET_ANDROID:
222 if (!display->getExtensions().framebufferTargetANDROID)
223 {
224 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANDROID_framebuffer_target is not enabled.";
225 }
226 break;
227
228 case EGL_BIND_TO_TEXTURE_TARGET_ANGLE:
229 if (!display->getExtensions().iosurfaceClientBuffer)
230 {
231 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_iosurface_client_buffer is not enabled.";
232 }
233 break;
234
235 case EGL_Y_INVERTED_NOK:
236 if (!display->getExtensions().textureFromPixmapNOK)
237 {
238 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_NOK_texture_from_pixmap is not enabled.";
239 }
240 break;
241
242 default:
243 return EglBadAttribute() << "Unknown attribute.";
244 }
245
246 return NoError();
247}
248
249Error ValidateConfigAttributeValue(const Display *display, EGLAttrib attribute, EGLAttrib value)
250{
251 switch (attribute)
252 {
253
254 case EGL_BIND_TO_TEXTURE_RGB:
255 case EGL_BIND_TO_TEXTURE_RGBA:
256 switch (value)
257 {
258 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
259 case EGL_TRUE:
260 case EGL_FALSE:
261 break;
262 default:
263 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_bind_to_texture invalid attribute: " << value;
264 }
265 break;
266
267 case EGL_COLOR_BUFFER_TYPE:
268 switch (value)
269 {
270 case EGL_RGB_BUFFER:
271 case EGL_LUMINANCE_BUFFER:
272 // EGL_DONT_CARE doesn't match the spec, but does match dEQP usage
273 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
274 break;
275 default:
276 return EglBadAttribute()
277 << "EGL_color_buffer_type invalid attribute: " << value;
278 }
279 break;
280
281 case EGL_NATIVE_RENDERABLE:
282 switch (value)
283 {
284 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
285 case EGL_TRUE:
286 case EGL_FALSE:
287 break;
288 default:
289 return EglBadAttribute()
290 << "EGL_native_renderable invalid attribute: " << value;
291 }
292 break;
293
294 case EGL_TRANSPARENT_TYPE:
295 switch (value)
296 {
297 case EGL_NONE:
298 case EGL_TRANSPARENT_RGB:
299 // EGL_DONT_CARE doesn't match the spec, but does match dEQP usage
300 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
301 break;
302 default:
303 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_transparent_type invalid attribute: " << value;
304 }
305 break;
306
307 case EGL_RECORDABLE_ANDROID:
308 switch (value)
309 {
310 case EGL_TRUE:
311 case EGL_FALSE:
312 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
313 break;
314 default:
315 return EglBadAttribute()
316 << "EGL_RECORDABLE_ANDROID invalid attribute: " << value;
317 }
318 break;
319
320 case EGL_COLOR_COMPONENT_TYPE_EXT:
321 switch (value)
322 {
323 case EGL_COLOR_COMPONENT_TYPE_FIXED_EXT:
324 case EGL_COLOR_COMPONENT_TYPE_FLOAT_EXT:
325 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
326 break;
327 default:
328 return EglBadAttribute()
329 << "EGL_COLOR_COMPONENT_TYPE_EXT invalid attribute: " << value;
330 }
331 break;
332
333 default:
334 break;
335 }
336
337 return NoError();
338}
339
340Error ValidateConfigAttributes(const Display *display, const AttributeMap &attributes)
341{
342 for (const auto &attrib : attributes)
343 {
344 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateConfigAttribute(display, attrib.first));
345 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateConfigAttributeValue(display, attrib.first, attrib.second));
346 }
347
348 return NoError();
349}

351Error ValidateColorspaceAttribute(const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions, EGLAttrib colorSpace)
352{
353 switch (colorSpace)
354 {
355 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_SRGB:
356 break;
357 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_LINEAR:
358 break;
359 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_DISPLAY_P3_LINEAR_EXT:
360 if (!displayExtensions.glColorspaceDisplayP3Linear)
361 {
362 return EglBadAttribute() << "EXT_gl_colorspace_display_p3_linear is not available.";
363 }
364 break;
365 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_DISPLAY_P3_EXT:
366 if (!displayExtensions.glColorspaceDisplayP3)
367 {
368 return EglBadAttribute() << "EXT_gl_colorspace_display_p3 is not available.";
369 }
370 break;
371 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_DISPLAY_P3_PASSTHROUGH_EXT:
372 if (!displayExtensions.glColorspaceDisplayP3Passthrough)
373 {
374 return EglBadAttribute()
375 << "EGL_EXT_gl_colorspace_display_p3_passthrough is not available.";
376 }
377 break;
378 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_SCRGB_EXT:
379 if (!displayExtensions.glColorspaceScrgb)
380 {
381 return EglBadAttribute() << "EXT_gl_colorspace_scrgb is not available.";
382 }
383 break;
384 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_SCRGB_LINEAR_EXT:
385 if (!displayExtensions.glColorspaceScrgbLinear)
386 {
387 return EglBadAttribute() << "EXT_gl_colorspace_scrgb_linear is not available.";
388 }
389 break;
390 default:
391 return EglBadAttribute();
392 }
393 return NoError();
394}
395Error ValidatePlatformType(const ClientExtensions &clientExtensions, EGLAttrib platformType)
396{
397 switch (platformType)
398 {
399 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_DEFAULT_ANGLE:
400 break;
401
402 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D9_ANGLE:
403 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE:
404 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLED3D)
405 {
406 return EglBadAttribute() << "Direct3D platform is unsupported.";
407 }
408 break;
409
410 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_OPENGL_ANGLE:
411 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_OPENGLES_ANGLE:
412 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLEOpenGL)
413 {
414 return EglBadAttribute() << "OpenGL platform is unsupported.";
415 }
416 break;
417
418 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_NULL_ANGLE:
419 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLENULL)
420 {
421 return EglBadAttribute() << "Display type EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_NULL_ANGLE "
422 "requires EGL_ANGLE_platform_angle_null.";
423 }
424 break;
425
426 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_VULKAN_ANGLE:
427 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLEVulkan)
428 {
429 return EglBadAttribute() << "Vulkan platform is unsupported.";
430 }
431 break;
432
433 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_METAL_ANGLE:
434 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLEMetal)
435 {
436 return EglBadAttribute() << "Metal platform is unsupported.";
437 }
438 break;
439
440 default:
441 return EglBadAttribute() << "Unknown platform type.";
442 }
443
444 return NoError();
445}
446
447Error ValidateGetPlatformDisplayCommon(EGLenum platform,
448 void *native_display,
449 const AttributeMap &attribMap)
450{
451 const ClientExtensions &clientExtensions = Display::GetClientExtensions();
452
453 switch (platform)
454 {
455 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_ANGLE:
456 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLE)
457 {
458 return EglBadParameter() << "Platform ANGLE extension is not active";
459 }
460 break;
461 case EGL_PLATFORM_DEVICE_EXT:
462 if (!clientExtensions.platformDevice)
463 {
464 return EglBadParameter() << "Platform Device extension is not active";
465 }
466 break;
467 default:
468 return EglBadConfig() << "Bad platform type.";
469 }
470
471 if (platform == EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_ANGLE)
472 {
473 EGLAttrib platformType = EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_DEFAULT_ANGLE;
474 bool enableAutoTrimSpecified = false;
475 bool enableD3D11on12 = false;
476 bool presentPathSpecified = false;
477 bool luidSpecified = false;
478
479 Optional<EGLAttrib> majorVersion;
480 Optional<EGLAttrib> minorVersion;
481 Optional<EGLAttrib> deviceType;
482 Optional<EGLAttrib> eglHandle;
483
484 for (const auto &curAttrib : attribMap)
485 {
486 const EGLAttrib value = curAttrib.second;
487
488 switch (curAttrib.first)
489 {
490 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_ANGLE:
491 {
492 ANGLE_TRY(ValidatePlatformType(clientExtensions, value));
493 platformType = value;
494 break;
495 }
496
497 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_MAX_VERSION_MAJOR_ANGLE:
498 if (value != EGL_DONT_CARE)
499 {
500 majorVersion = value;
501 }
502 break;
503
504 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_MAX_VERSION_MINOR_ANGLE:
505 if (value != EGL_DONT_CARE)
506 {
507 minorVersion = value;
508 }
509 break;
510
511 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_ENABLE_AUTOMATIC_TRIM_ANGLE:
512 switch (value)
513 {
514 case EGL_TRUE:
515 case EGL_FALSE:
516 break;
517 default:
518 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid automatic trim attribute";
519 }
520 enableAutoTrimSpecified = true;
521 break;
522
523 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D11ON12_ANGLE:
524 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLED3D ||
525 !clientExtensions.platformANGLED3D11ON12)
526 {
527 return EglBadAttribute()
528 << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D11ON12_ANGLE extension not active.";
529 }
530
531 switch (value)
532 {
533 case EGL_TRUE:
534 case EGL_FALSE:
535 break;
536 default:
537 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid D3D11on12 attribute";
538 }
539 enableD3D11on12 = true;
540 break;
541
542 case EGL_EXPERIMENTAL_PRESENT_PATH_ANGLE:
543 if (!clientExtensions.experimentalPresentPath)
544 {
545 return EglBadAttribute()
546 << "EGL_ANGLE_experimental_present_path extension not active";
547 }
548
549 switch (value)
550 {
551 case EGL_EXPERIMENTAL_PRESENT_PATH_FAST_ANGLE:
552 case EGL_EXPERIMENTAL_PRESENT_PATH_COPY_ANGLE:
553 break;
554 default:
555 return EglBadAttribute()
556 << "Invalid value for EGL_EXPERIMENTAL_PRESENT_PATH_ANGLE";
557 }
558 presentPathSpecified = true;
559 break;
560
561 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_ANGLE:
562 switch (value)
563 {
564 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_HARDWARE_ANGLE:
565 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_NULL_ANGLE:
566 break;
567
568 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_WARP_ANGLE:
569 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_REFERENCE_ANGLE:
570 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLED3D)
571 {
572 return EglBadAttribute()
573 << "EGL_ANGLE_platform_angle_d3d is not supported";
574 }
575 break;
576
577 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_EGL_ANGLE:
578 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLEDeviceTypeEGLANGLE)
579 {
580 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_platform_angle_device_type_"
581 "egl_angle is not supported";
582 }
583 break;
584
585 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_SWIFTSHADER_ANGLE:
586 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLEDeviceTypeSwiftShader)
587 {
588 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_platform_angle_device_type_"
589 "swiftshader is not supported";
590 }
591 break;
592
593 default:
594 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid value for "
595 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_ANGLE "
596 "attrib";
597 }
598 deviceType = value;
599 break;
600
601 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEBUG_LAYERS_ENABLED_ANGLE:
602 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLE)
603 {
604 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_platform_angle extension not active";
605 }
606 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE && value != EGL_DONT_CARE)
607 {
608 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEBUG_LAYERS_ENABLED_ANGLE "
609 "must be EGL_TRUE, EGL_FALSE, or "
610 "EGL_DONT_CARE.";
611 }
612 break;
613
614 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_EGL_HANDLE_ANGLE:
615 if (value != EGL_DONT_CARE)
616 {
617 eglHandle = value;
618 }
619 break;
620
621 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_CONTEXT_VIRTUALIZATION_ANGLE:
622 if (!clientExtensions.platformANGLEContextVirtualization)
623 {
624 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_platform_angle_context_"
625 "virtualization extension not active";
626 }
627
628 switch (value)
629 {
630 case EGL_DONT_CARE:
631 case EGL_FALSE:
632 case EGL_TRUE:
633 break;
634
635 default:
636 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid value for "
637 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_CONTEXT_VIRTUALIZATION_"
638 "ANGLE attrib";
639 }
640 break;
641
642 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_HIGH_ANGLE:
643 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_LOW_ANGLE:
644 luidSpecified = true;
645 break;
646 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_CONTEXT_VOLATILE_EAGL_ANGLE:
647 // The property does not have an effect if it's not active, so do not check
648 // for non-support.
649 switch (value)
650 {
651 case EGL_FALSE:
652 case EGL_TRUE:
653 break;
654 default:
655 return EglBadAttribute()
656 << "Invalid value for "
657 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_CONTEXT_VOLATILE_"
658 "EAGL_ANGLE attrib";
659 }
660 break;
661 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_CONTEXT_VOLATILE_CGL_ANGLE:
662 // The property does not have an effect if it's not active, so do not check
663 // for non-support.
664 switch (value)
665 {
666 case EGL_FALSE:
667 case EGL_TRUE:
668 break;
669 default:
670 return EglBadAttribute()
671 << "Invalid value for "
672 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_CONTEXT_VOLATILE_"
673 "CGL_ANGLE attrib";
674 }
675 break;
676 default:
677 break;
678 }
679 }
680
681 if (!majorVersion.valid() && minorVersion.valid())
682 {
683 return EglBadAttribute()
684 << "Must specify major version if you specify a minor version.";
685 }
686
687 if (deviceType == EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_WARP_ANGLE &&
688 platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE)
689 {
690 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_WARP_ANGLE requires a "
691 "device type of EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE.";
692 }
693
694 if (enableAutoTrimSpecified && platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE)
695 {
696 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_ENABLE_AUTOMATIC_TRIM_ANGLE "
697 "requires a device type of "
698 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE.";
699 }
700
701 if (enableD3D11on12)
702 {
703 if (platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE)
704 {
705 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D11ON12_ANGLE "
706 "requires a platform type of "
707 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE.";
708 }
709
710 if (deviceType.valid() && deviceType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_HARDWARE_ANGLE &&
711 deviceType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_WARP_ANGLE)
712 {
713 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D11ON12_ANGLE requires a device "
714 "type of EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_HARDWARE_ANGLE "
715 "or EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_WARP_ANGLE";
716 }
717 }
718
719 if (presentPathSpecified && platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE)
720 {
721 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_EXPERIMENTAL_PRESENT_PATH_ANGLE requires a "
722 "device type of EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE.";
723 }
724
725 if (luidSpecified)
726 {
727 if (platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE)
728 {
729 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_HIGH_ANGLE and "
730 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_LOW_ANGLE "
731 "require a platform type of "
732 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE.";
733 }
734
735 if (attribMap.get(EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_HIGH_ANGLE, 0) == 0 &&
736 attribMap.get(EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_LOW_ANGLE, 0) == 0)
737 {
738 return EglBadAttribute() << "If either EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_HIGH_ANGLE "
739 "and/or EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_D3D_LUID_LOW_ANGLE are "
740 "specified, at least one must non-zero.";
741 }
742 }
743
744 if (deviceType.valid())
745 {
746 switch (deviceType.value())
747 {
748 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_REFERENCE_ANGLE:
749 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_D3D_WARP_ANGLE:
750 if (platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D9_ANGLE &&
751 platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D11_ANGLE)
752 {
753 return EglBadAttribute()
754 << "This device type requires a "
755 "platform type of EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D9_ANGLE or "
756 "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_D3D9_ANGLE.";
757 }
758 break;
759
760 case EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_DEVICE_TYPE_SWIFTSHADER_ANGLE:
761 if (platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_VULKAN_ANGLE)
762 {
763 return EglBadAttribute()
764 << "This device type requires a "
765 "platform type of EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_VULKAN_ANGLE.";
766 }
767 break;
768
769 default:
770 break;
771 }
772 }
773
774 if (platformType == EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_VULKAN_ANGLE)
775 {
776 if ((majorVersion.valid() && majorVersion.value() != 1) ||
777 (minorVersion.valid() && minorVersion.value() != 0))
778 {
779 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_VULKAN_ANGLE currently "
780 "only supports Vulkan 1.0.";
781 }
782 }
783
784 if (eglHandle.valid() && platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_OPENGLES_ANGLE &&
785 platformType != EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_DEFAULT_ANGLE)
786 {
787 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_EGL_HANDLE_ANGLE requires a "
788 "device type of EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_TYPE_OPENGLES_ANGLE.";
789 }
790 }
791 else if (platform == EGL_PLATFORM_DEVICE_EXT)
792 {
793 Device *eglDevice = static_cast<Device *>(native_display);
794 if (eglDevice == nullptr || !Device::IsValidDevice(eglDevice))
795 {
796 return EglBadAttribute() << "native_display should be a valid EGL device if "
797 "platform equals EGL_PLATFORM_DEVICE_EXT";
798 }
799 }
800 else
801 {
802 UNREACHABLE();
803 }
804
805 if (attribMap.contains(EGL_FEATURE_OVERRIDES_ENABLED_ANGLE))
806 {
807 if (!clientExtensions.featureControlANGLE)
808 {
809 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_feature_control is not supported";
810 }
811 else if (attribMap.get(EGL_FEATURE_OVERRIDES_ENABLED_ANGLE, 0) == 0)
812 {
813 return EglBadAttribute()
814 << "EGL_FEATURE_OVERRIDES_ENABLED_ANGLE must be a valid pointer";
815 }
816 }
817 if (attribMap.contains(EGL_FEATURE_OVERRIDES_DISABLED_ANGLE))
818 {
819 if (!clientExtensions.featureControlANGLE)
820 {
821 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_feature_control is not supported";
822 }
823 else if (attribMap.get(EGL_FEATURE_OVERRIDES_DISABLED_ANGLE, 0) == 0)
824 {
825 return EglBadAttribute()
826 << "EGL_FEATURE_OVERRIDES_DISABLED_ANGLE must be a valid pointer";
827 }
828 }
829
830 return NoError();
831}

833Error ValidateStream(const Display *display, const Stream *stream)
834{
835 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
836
837 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
838 if (!displayExtensions.stream)
839 {
840 return EglBadAccess() << "Stream extension not active";
841 }
842
843 if (stream == EGL_NO_STREAM_KHR || !display->isValidStream(stream))
844 {
845 return EglBadStream() << "Invalid stream";
846 }
847
848 return NoError();
849}

851Error ValidateLabeledObject(Thread *thread,
852 const Display *display,
853 ObjectType objectType,
854 EGLObjectKHR object,
855 LabeledObject **outLabeledObject)
856{
857 switch (objectType)
858 {
859 case ObjectType::Context:
860 {
861 gl::Context *context = static_cast<gl::Context *>(object);
862 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
863 *outLabeledObject = context;
864 break;
865 }
866
867 case ObjectType::Display:
868 {
869 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
870 if (display != object)
871 {
872 return EglBadParameter() << "when object type is EGL_OBJECT_DISPLAY_KHR, the "
873 "object must be the same as the display.";
874 }
875
876 *outLabeledObject = static_cast<Display *>(object);
877 break;
878 }
879
880 case ObjectType::Image:
881 {
882 Image *image = static_cast<Image *>(object);
883 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateImage(display, image));
884 *outLabeledObject = image;
885 break;
886 }
887
888 case ObjectType::Stream:
889 {
890 Stream *stream = static_cast<Stream *>(object);
891 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateStream(display, stream));
892 *outLabeledObject = stream;
893 break;
894 }
895
896 case ObjectType::Surface:
897 {
898 Surface *surface = static_cast<Surface *>(object);
899 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSurface(display, surface));
900 *outLabeledObject = surface;
901 break;
902 }
903
904 case ObjectType::Sync:
905 {
906 Sync *sync = static_cast<Sync *>(object);
907 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSync(display, sync));
908 *outLabeledObject = sync;
909 break;
910 }
911
912 case ObjectType::Thread:
913 {
914 *outLabeledObject = thread;
915 break;
916 }
917
918 default:
919 return EglBadParameter() << "unknown object type.";
920 }
921
922 return NoError();
923}

1168
1169Error ValidateCreateContext(Display *display,
1170 Config *configuration,
1171 gl::Context *shareContext,
1172 const AttributeMap &attributes)
1173{
1174 if (configuration)
1175 {
1176 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateConfig(display, configuration));
1177 }
1178 else
1179 {
1180 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
1181 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
1182 if (!displayExtensions.noConfigContext)
1183 {
1184 return EglBadConfig();
1185 }
1186 }
1187
1188 // Get the requested client version (default is 1) and check it is 2 or 3.
1189 EGLAttrib clientMajorVersion = 1;
1190 EGLAttrib clientMinorVersion = 0;
1191 EGLAttrib contextFlags = 0;
1192 bool resetNotification = false;
1193 for (AttributeMap::const_iterator attributeIter = attributes.begin();
1194 attributeIter != attributes.end(); attributeIter++)
1195 {
1196 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter->first;
1197 EGLAttrib value = attributeIter->second;
1198
1199 switch (attribute)
1200 {
1201 case EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_VERSION:
1202 clientMajorVersion = value;
1203 break;
1204
1205 case EGL_CONTEXT_MINOR_VERSION:
1206 clientMinorVersion = value;
1207 break;
1208
1209 case EGL_CONTEXT_FLAGS_KHR:
1210 contextFlags = value;
1211 break;
1212
1213 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_DEBUG:
1214 break;
1215
1216 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_PROFILE_MASK_KHR:
1217 // Only valid for OpenGL (non-ES) contexts
1218 return EglBadAttribute();
1219
1220 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_ROBUST_ACCESS_EXT:
1221 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextRobustness)
1222 {
1223 return EglBadAttribute();
1224 }
1225 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1226 {
1227 return EglBadAttribute();
1228 }
1229 break;
1230
1231 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_RESET_NOTIFICATION_STRATEGY_KHR:
1232 return EglBadAttribute()
1233 << "EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_RESET_NOTIFICATION_STRATEGY_KHR is not"
1234 << " valid for GLES with EGL 1.4 and KHR_create_context. Use"
1235 << " EXT_create_context_robustness.";
1236 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_RESET_NOTIFICATION_STRATEGY_EXT:
1237 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextRobustness)
1238 {
1239 return EglBadAttribute();
1240 }
1241 if (value == EGL_LOSE_CONTEXT_ON_RESET_EXT)
1242 {
1243 resetNotification = true;
1244 }
1245 else if (value != EGL_NO_RESET_NOTIFICATION_EXT)
1246 {
1247 return EglBadAttribute();
1248 }
1249 break;
1250
1251 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_NO_ERROR_KHR:
1252 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextNoError)
1253 {
1254 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid Context attribute.";
1255 }
1256 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1257 {
1258 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute must be EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1259 }
1260 break;
1261
1262 case EGL_CONTEXT_WEBGL_COMPATIBILITY_ANGLE:
1263 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextWebGLCompatibility)
1264 {
1265 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute "
1266 "EGL_CONTEXT_WEBGL_COMPATIBILITY_ANGLE requires "
1267 "EGL_ANGLE_create_context_webgl_compatibility.";
1268 }
1269 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1270 {
1271 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_CONTEXT_WEBGL_COMPATIBILITY_ANGLE must be "
1272 "EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1273 }
1274 break;
1275
1276 case EGL_CONTEXT_BIND_GENERATES_RESOURCE_CHROMIUM:
1277 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextBindGeneratesResource)
1278 {
1279 return EglBadAttribute()
1280 << "Attribute EGL_CONTEXT_BIND_GENERATES_RESOURCE_CHROMIUM requires "
1281 "EGL_CHROMIUM_create_context_bind_generates_resource.";
1282 }
1283 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1284 {
1285 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_CONTEXT_BIND_GENERATES_RESOURCE_CHROMIUM "
1286 "must be EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1287 }
1288 break;
1289
1290 case EGL_DISPLAY_TEXTURE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE:
1291 if (!display->getExtensions().displayTextureShareGroup)
1292 {
1293 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute "
1294 "EGL_DISPLAY_TEXTURE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE requires "
1295 "EGL_ANGLE_display_texture_share_group.";
1296 }
1297 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1298 {
1299 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_DISPLAY_TEXTURE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE must be "
1300 "EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1301 }
1302 if (shareContext &&
1303 (shareContext->usingDisplayTextureShareGroup() != (value == EGL_TRUE)))
1304 {
1305 return EglBadAttribute() << "All contexts within a share group must be "
1306 "created with the same value of "
1307 "EGL_DISPLAY_TEXTURE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE.";
1308 }
1309 break;
1310
1311 case EGL_DISPLAY_SEMAPHORE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE:
1312 if (!display->getExtensions().displayTextureShareGroup)
1313 {
1314 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute "
1315 "EGL_DISPLAY_SEMAPHORE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE requires "
1316 "EGL_ANGLE_display_semaphore_share_group.";
1317 }
1318 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1319 {
1320 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_DISPLAY_SEMAPHORE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE must be "
1321 "EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1322 }
1323 if (shareContext &&
1324 (shareContext->usingDisplaySemaphoreShareGroup() != (value == EGL_TRUE)))
1325 {
1326 return EglBadAttribute() << "All contexts within a share group must be "
1327 "created with the same value of "
1328 "EGL_DISPLAY_SEMAPHORE_SHARE_GROUP_ANGLE.";
1329 }
1330 break;
1331
1332 case EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_ARRAYS_ENABLED_ANGLE:
1333 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextClientArrays)
1334 {
1335 return EglBadAttribute()
1336 << "Attribute EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_ARRAYS_ENABLED_ANGLE requires "
1337 "EGL_ANGLE_create_context_client_arrays.";
1338 }
1339 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1340 {
1341 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_ARRAYS_ENABLED_ANGLE must "
1342 "be EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1343 }
1344 break;
1345
1346 case EGL_CONTEXT_PROGRAM_BINARY_CACHE_ENABLED_ANGLE:
1347 if (!display->getExtensions().programCacheControl)
1348 {
1349 return EglBadAttribute()
1350 << "Attribute EGL_CONTEXT_PROGRAM_BINARY_CACHE_ENABLED_ANGLE "
1351 "requires EGL_ANGLE_program_cache_control.";
1352 }
1353 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1354 {
1355 return EglBadAttribute()
1356 << "EGL_CONTEXT_PROGRAM_BINARY_CACHE_ENABLED_ANGLE must "
1357 "be EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1358 }
1359 break;
1360
1361 case EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE:
1362 if (!display->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization)
1363 {
1364 return EglBadAttribute()
1365 << "Attribute EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE "
1366 "requires EGL_ANGLE_robust_resource_initialization.";
1367 }
1368 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1369 {
1370 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE must be "
1371 "either EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1372 }
1373 break;
1374
1375 case EGL_EXTENSIONS_ENABLED_ANGLE:
1376 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextExtensionsEnabled)
1377 {
1378 return EglBadAttribute()
1379 << "Attribute EGL_EXTENSIONS_ENABLED_ANGLE "
1380 "requires EGL_ANGLE_create_context_extensions_enabled.";
1381 }
1382 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1383 {
1384 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_EXTENSIONS_ENABLED_ANGLE must be "
1385 "either EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1386 }
1387 break;
1388
1389 case EGL_POWER_PREFERENCE_ANGLE:
1390 if (!display->getExtensions().powerPreference)
1391 {
1392 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute EGL_POWER_PREFERENCE_ANGLE "
1393 "requires EGL_ANGLE_power_preference.";
1394 }
1395 if (value != EGL_LOW_POWER_ANGLE && value != EGL_HIGH_POWER_ANGLE)
1396 {
1397 return EglBadAttribute()
1398 << "EGL_POWER_PREFERENCE_ANGLE must be "
1399 "either EGL_LOW_POWER_ANGLE or EGL_HIGH_POWER_ANGLE.";
1400 }
1401 break;
1402
1403 case EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_BACKWARDS_COMPATIBLE_ANGLE:
1404 if (!display->getExtensions().createContextBackwardsCompatible)
1405 {
1406 return EglBadAttribute()
1407 << "Attribute EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_BACKWARDS_COMPATIBLE_ANGLE "
1408 "requires EGL_ANGLE_create_context_backwards_compatible.";
1409 }
1410 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1411 {
1412 return EglBadAttribute()
1413 << "EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_BACKWARDS_COMPATIBLE_ANGLE must be "
1414 "either EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1415 }
1416 break;
1417
1418 case EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LEVEL_IMG:
1419 if (!display->getExtensions().contextPriority)
1420 {
1421 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LEVEL_IMG requires "
1422 "extension EGL_IMG_context_priority.";
1423 }
1424 switch (value)
1425 {
1426 case EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LOW_IMG:
1427 case EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_MEDIUM_IMG:
1428 case EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_HIGH_IMG:
1429 break;
1430 default:
1431 return EglBadAttribute() << "Attribute EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LEVEL_IMG "
1432 "must be one of: EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LOW_IMG, "
1433 "EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_MEDIUM_IMG, or "
1434 "EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_HIGH_IMG.";
1435 }
1436 break;
1437
1438 case EGL_GENERATE_RESET_ON_VIDEO_MEMORY_PURGE_NV:
1439 if (!display->getExtensions().robustnessVideoMemoryPurgeNV)
1440 {
1441 return EglBadAttribute()
1442 << "Attribute EGL_GENERATE_RESET_ON_VIDEO_MEMORY_PURGE_NV requires "
1443 "extension EGL_NV_robustness_video_memory_purge.";
1444 }
1445 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1446 {
1447 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_GENERATE_RESET_ON_VIDEO_MEMORY_PURGE_NV must "
1448 "be either EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1449 }
1450 break;
1451
1452 default:
1453 return EglBadAttribute() << "Unknown attribute.";
1454 }
1455 }
1456
1457 switch (clientMajorVersion)
1458 {
1459 case 1:
1460 if (clientMinorVersion != 0 && clientMinorVersion != 1)
1461 {
1462 return EglBadAttribute();
1463 }
1464 if (configuration == EGL_NO_CONFIG_KHR)
1465 {
1466 return EglBadMatch();
1467 }
1468 if ((configuration != EGL_NO_CONFIG_KHR) &&
1469 !(configuration->renderableType & EGL_OPENGL_ES_BIT))
1470 {
1471 return EglBadMatch();
1472 }
1473 break;
1474
1475 case 2:
1476 if (clientMinorVersion != 0)
1477 {
1478 return EglBadAttribute();
1479 }
1480 if ((configuration != EGL_NO_CONFIG_KHR) &&
1481 !(configuration->renderableType & EGL_OPENGL_ES2_BIT))
1482 {
1483 return EglBadMatch();
1484 }
1485 break;
1486 case 3:
1487 if (clientMinorVersion != 0 && clientMinorVersion != 1)
1488 {
1489 return EglBadAttribute();
1490 }
1491 if ((configuration != EGL_NO_CONFIG_KHR) &&
1492 !(configuration->renderableType & EGL_OPENGL_ES3_BIT))
1493 {
1494 return EglBadMatch();
1495 }
1496 if (display->getMaxSupportedESVersion() <
1497 gl::Version(static_cast<GLuint>(clientMajorVersion),
1498 static_cast<GLuint>(clientMinorVersion)))
1499 {
1500 return EglBadAttribute() << "Requested GLES version is not supported.";
1501 }
1502 break;
1503 default:
1504 return EglBadAttribute();
1505 break;
1506 }
1507
1508 // Note: EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_FORWARD_COMPATIBLE_BIT_KHR does not apply to ES
1509 const EGLint validContextFlags =
1510 (EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_DEBUG_BIT_KHR | EGL_CONTEXT_OPENGL_ROBUST_ACCESS_BIT_KHR);
1511 if ((contextFlags & ~validContextFlags) != 0)
1512 {
1513 return EglBadAttribute();
1514 }
1515
1516 if (shareContext)
1517 {
1518 // Shared context is invalid or is owned by another display
1519 if (!display->isValidContext(shareContext))
1520 {
1521 return EglBadMatch();
1522 }
1523
1524 if (shareContext->isResetNotificationEnabled() != resetNotification)
1525 {
1526 return EglBadMatch();
1527 }
1528 }
1529
1530 return NoError();
1531}

1533Error ValidateCreateWindowSurface(Display *display,
1534 Config *config,
1535 EGLNativeWindowType window,
1536 const AttributeMap &attributes)
1537{
1538 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateConfig(display, config));
1539
1540 if (!display->isValidNativeWindow(window))
1541 {
1542 return EglBadNativeWindow();
1543 }
1544
1545 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
1546
1547 for (AttributeMap::const_iterator attributeIter = attributes.begin();
1548 attributeIter != attributes.end(); attributeIter++)
1549 {
1550 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter->first;
1551 EGLAttrib value = attributeIter->second;
1552
1553 switch (attribute)
1554 {
1555 case EGL_RENDER_BUFFER:
1556 switch (value)
1557 {
1558 case EGL_BACK_BUFFER:
1559 break;
1560 case EGL_SINGLE_BUFFER:
1561 return EglBadMatch(); // Rendering directly to front buffer not supported
1562 default:
1563 return EglBadAttribute();
1564 }
1565 break;
1566
1567 case EGL_POST_SUB_BUFFER_SUPPORTED_NV:
1568 if (!displayExtensions.postSubBuffer)
1569 {
1570 return EglBadAttribute();
1571 }
1572 break;
1573
1574 case EGL_FLEXIBLE_SURFACE_COMPATIBILITY_SUPPORTED_ANGLE:
1575 if (!displayExtensions.flexibleSurfaceCompatibility)
1576 {
1577 return EglBadAttribute();
1578 }
1579 break;
1580
1581 case EGL_WIDTH:
1582 case EGL_HEIGHT:
1583 if (!displayExtensions.windowFixedSize)
1584 {
1585 return EglBadAttribute();
1586 }
1587 if (value < 0)
1588 {
1589 return EglBadParameter();
1590 }
1591 break;
1592
1593 case EGL_FIXED_SIZE_ANGLE:
1594 if (!displayExtensions.windowFixedSize)
1595 {
1596 return EglBadAttribute();
1597 }
1598 break;
1599
1600 case EGL_SURFACE_ORIENTATION_ANGLE:
1601 if (!displayExtensions.surfaceOrientation)
1602 {
1603 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ANGLE_surface_orientation is not enabled.";
1604 }
1605 break;
1606
1607 case EGL_VG_COLORSPACE:
1608 return EglBadMatch();
1609
1610 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE:
1611 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateColorspaceAttribute(displayExtensions, value));
1612 break;
1613
1614 case EGL_VG_ALPHA_FORMAT:
1615 return EglBadMatch();
1616
1617 case EGL_DIRECT_COMPOSITION_ANGLE:
1618 if (!displayExtensions.directComposition)
1619 {
1620 return EglBadAttribute();
1621 }
1622 break;
1623
1624 case EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE:
1625 if (!display->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization)
1626 {
1627 return EglBadAttribute()
1628 << "Attribute EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE "
1629 "requires EGL_ANGLE_robust_resource_initialization.";
1630 }
1631 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1632 {
1633 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE must be "
1634 "either EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1635 }
1636 break;
1637
1638 case EGL_GGP_STREAM_DESCRIPTOR_ANGLE:
1639 if (!display->getExtensions().ggpStreamDescriptor)
1640 {
1641 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_GGP_STREAM_DESCRIPTOR_ANGLE requires "
1642 "EGL_ANGLE_ggp_stream_descriptor.";
1643 }
1644 break;
1645
1646 default:
1647 return EglBadAttribute();
1648 }
1649 }
1650
1651 if (Display::hasExistingWindowSurface(window))
1652 {
1653 return EglBadAlloc();
1654 }
1655
1656 return NoError();
1657}

1659Error ValidateCreatePbufferSurface(Display *display, Config *config, const AttributeMap &attributes)
1660{
1661 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateConfig(display, config));
1662
1663 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
1664
1665 for (AttributeMap::const_iterator attributeIter = attributes.begin();
1666 attributeIter != attributes.end(); attributeIter++)
1667 {
1668 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter->first;
1669 EGLAttrib value = attributeIter->second;
1670
1671 switch (attribute)
1672 {
1673 case EGL_WIDTH:
1674 case EGL_HEIGHT:
1675 if (value < 0)
1676 {
1677 return EglBadParameter();
1678 }
1679 break;
1680
1681 case EGL_LARGEST_PBUFFER:
1682 break;
1683
1684 case EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT:
1685 switch (value)
1686 {
1687 case EGL_NO_TEXTURE:
1688 case EGL_TEXTURE_RGB:
1689 case EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA:
1690 break;
1691 default:
1692 return EglBadAttribute();
1693 }
1694 break;
1695
1696 case EGL_TEXTURE_TARGET:
1697 switch (value)
1698 {
1699 case EGL_NO_TEXTURE:
1700 case EGL_TEXTURE_2D:
1701 break;
1702 default:
1703 return EglBadAttribute();
1704 }
1705 break;
1706
1707 case EGL_MIPMAP_TEXTURE:
1708 break;
1709
1710 case EGL_VG_COLORSPACE:
1711 break;
1712
1713 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE:
1714 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateColorspaceAttribute(displayExtensions, value));
1715 break;
1716
1717 case EGL_VG_ALPHA_FORMAT:
1718 break;
1719
1720 case EGL_FLEXIBLE_SURFACE_COMPATIBILITY_SUPPORTED_ANGLE:
1721 if (!displayExtensions.flexibleSurfaceCompatibility)
1722 {
1723 return EglBadAttribute()
1724 << "EGL_FLEXIBLE_SURFACE_COMPATIBILITY_SUPPORTED_ANGLE cannot be used "
1725 "without EGL_ANGLE_flexible_surface_compatibility support.";
1726 }
1727 break;
1728
1729 case EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE:
1730 if (!display->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization)
1731 {
1732 return EglBadAttribute()
1733 << "Attribute EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE "
1734 "requires EGL_ANGLE_robust_resource_initialization.";
1735 }
1736 if (value != EGL_TRUE && value != EGL_FALSE)
1737 {
1738 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE must be "
1739 "either EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
1740 }
1741 break;
1742
1743 default:
1744 return EglBadAttribute();
1745 }
1746 }
1747
1748 if (!(config->surfaceType & EGL_PBUFFER_BIT))
1749 {
1750 return EglBadMatch();
1751 }
1752
1753 const Caps &caps = display->getCaps();
1754
1755 EGLAttrib textureFormat = attributes.get(EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT, EGL_NO_TEXTURE);
1756 EGLAttrib textureTarget = attributes.get(EGL_TEXTURE_TARGET, EGL_NO_TEXTURE);
1757
1758 if ((textureFormat != EGL_NO_TEXTURE && textureTarget == EGL_NO_TEXTURE) ||
1759 (textureFormat == EGL_NO_TEXTURE && textureTarget != EGL_NO_TEXTURE))
1760 {
1761 return EglBadMatch();
1762 }
1763
1764 if ((textureFormat == EGL_TEXTURE_RGB && config->bindToTextureRGB != EGL_TRUE) ||
1765 (textureFormat == EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA && config->bindToTextureRGBA != EGL_TRUE))
1766 {
1767 return EglBadAttribute();
1768 }
1769
1770 EGLint width = static_cast<EGLint>(attributes.get(EGL_WIDTH, 0));
1771 EGLint height = static_cast<EGLint>(attributes.get(EGL_HEIGHT, 0));
1772 if (textureFormat != EGL_NO_TEXTURE && !caps.textureNPOT &&
1773 (!gl::isPow2(width) || !gl::isPow2(height)))
1774 {
1775 return EglBadMatch();
1776 }
1777
1778 return NoError();
1779}

1781Error ValidateCreatePbufferFromClientBuffer(Display *display,
1782 EGLenum buftype,
1783 EGLClientBuffer buffer,
1784 Config *config,
1785 const AttributeMap &attributes)
1786{
1787 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateConfig(display, config));
1788
1789 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
1790
1791 switch (buftype)
1792 {
1793 case EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_2D_SHARE_HANDLE_ANGLE:
1794 if (!displayExtensions.d3dShareHandleClientBuffer)
1795 {
1796 return EglBadParameter();
1797 }
1798 if (buffer == nullptr)
1799 {
1800 return EglBadParameter();
1801 }
1802 break;
1803
1804 case EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_ANGLE:
1805 if (!displayExtensions.d3dTextureClientBuffer)
1806 {
1807 return EglBadParameter();
1808 }
1809 if (buffer == nullptr)
1810 {
1811 return EglBadParameter();
1812 }
1813 break;
1814
1815 case EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE:
1816 if (!displayExtensions.iosurfaceClientBuffer)
1817 {
1818 return EglBadParameter() << "<buftype> EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE requires the "
1819 "EGL_ANGLE_iosurface_client_buffer extension.";
1820 }
1821 if (buffer == nullptr)
1822 {
1823 return EglBadParameter() << "<buffer> must be non null";
1824 }
1825 break;
1826
1827 default:
1828 return EglBadParameter();
1829 }
1830
1831 for (AttributeMap::const_iterator attributeIter = attributes.begin();
1832 attributeIter != attributes.end(); attributeIter++)
1833 {
1834 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter->first;
1835 EGLAttrib value = attributeIter->second;
1836
1837 switch (attribute)
1838 {
1839 case EGL_WIDTH:
1840 case EGL_HEIGHT:
1841 if (buftype != EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_2D_SHARE_HANDLE_ANGLE &&
1842 buftype != EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_ANGLE && buftype != EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE)
1843 {
1844 return EglBadParameter()
1845 << "Width and Height are not supported for thie <buftype>";
1846 }
1847 if (value < 0)
1848 {
1849 return EglBadParameter() << "Width and Height must be positive";
1850 }
1851 break;
1852
1853 case EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT:
1854 switch (value)
1855 {
1856 case EGL_NO_TEXTURE:
1857 case EGL_TEXTURE_RGB:
1858 case EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA:
1859 break;
1860 default:
1861 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid value for EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT";
1862 }
1863 break;
1864
1865 case EGL_TEXTURE_TARGET:
1866 switch (value)
1867 {
1868 case EGL_NO_TEXTURE:
1869 case EGL_TEXTURE_2D:
1870 break;
1871 case EGL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE_ANGLE:
1872 if (buftype != EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE)
1873 {
1874 return EglBadParameter()
1875 << "<buftype> doesn't support rectangle texture targets";
1876 }
1877 break;
1878
1879 default:
1880 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid value for EGL_TEXTURE_TARGET";
1881 }
1882 break;
1883
1884 case EGL_MIPMAP_TEXTURE:
1885 break;
1886
1887 case EGL_FLEXIBLE_SURFACE_COMPATIBILITY_SUPPORTED_ANGLE:
1888 if (!displayExtensions.flexibleSurfaceCompatibility)
1889 {
1890 return EglBadAttribute()
1891 << "EGL_FLEXIBLE_SURFACE_COMPATIBILITY_SUPPORTED_ANGLE cannot be used "
1892 "without EGL_ANGLE_flexible_surface_compatibility support.";
1893 }
1894 break;
1895
1896 case EGL_IOSURFACE_PLANE_ANGLE:
1897 if (buftype != EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE)
1898 {
1899 return EglBadAttribute() << "<buftype> doesn't support iosurface plane";
1900 }
1901 break;
1902
1903 case EGL_TEXTURE_TYPE_ANGLE:
1904 if (buftype != EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE)
1905 {
1906 return EglBadAttribute() << "<buftype> doesn't support texture type";
1907 }
1908 break;
1909
1910 case EGL_TEXTURE_INTERNAL_FORMAT_ANGLE:
1911 if (buftype != EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE && buftype != EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_ANGLE)
1912 {
1913 return EglBadAttribute() << "<buftype> doesn't support texture internal format";
1914 }
1915 break;
1916
1917 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE:
1918 if (buftype != EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_ANGLE)
1919 {
1920 return EglBadAttribute() << "<buftype> doesn't support setting GL colorspace";
1921 }
1922 break;
1923
1924 case EGL_IOSURFACE_USAGE_HINT_ANGLE:
1925 if (value & ~(EGL_IOSURFACE_READ_HINT_ANGLE | EGL_IOSURFACE_WRITE_HINT_ANGLE))
1926 {
1927 return EglBadAttribute()
1928 << "IOSurface usage hint must only contain READ or WRITE";
1929 }
1930 break;
1931
1932 case EGL_TEXTURE_OFFSET_X_ANGLE:
1933 case EGL_TEXTURE_OFFSET_Y_ANGLE:
1934 if (buftype != EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_ANGLE)
1935 {
1936 return EglBadAttribute() << "<buftype> doesn't support setting texture offset";
1937 }
1938 if (value < 0)
1939 {
1940 return EglBadAttribute() << "Texture offset cannot be negative";
1941 }
1942 break;
1943
1944 default:
1945 return EglBadAttribute();
1946 }
1947 }
1948
1949 EGLAttrib colorspace = attributes.get(EGL_GL_COLORSPACE, EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_LINEAR);
1950 if (colorspace != EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_LINEAR && colorspace != EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_SRGB)
1951 {
1952 return EglBadAttribute() << "invalid GL colorspace";
1953 }
1954
1955 if (!(config->surfaceType & EGL_PBUFFER_BIT))
1956 {
1957 return EglBadMatch();
1958 }
1959
1960 EGLAttrib textureFormat = attributes.get(EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT, EGL_NO_TEXTURE);
1961 EGLAttrib textureTarget = attributes.get(EGL_TEXTURE_TARGET, EGL_NO_TEXTURE);
1962 if ((textureFormat != EGL_NO_TEXTURE && textureTarget == EGL_NO_TEXTURE) ||
1963 (textureFormat == EGL_NO_TEXTURE && textureTarget != EGL_NO_TEXTURE))
1964 {
1965 return EglBadMatch();
1966 }
1967 if ((textureFormat == EGL_TEXTURE_RGB && config->bindToTextureRGB != EGL_TRUE) ||
1968 (textureFormat == EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA && config->bindToTextureRGBA != EGL_TRUE))
1969 {
1970 // TODO(cwallez@chromium.org): For IOSurface pbuffers we require that EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA is
1971 // set so that eglBindTexImage works. Normally this is only allowed if the config exposes
1972 // the bindToTextureRGB/RGBA flag. This issue is that enabling this flags means that
1973 // eglBindTexImage should also work for regular pbuffers which isn't implemented on macOS.
1974 // Instead of adding the flag we special case the check here to be ignored for IOSurfaces.
1975 // The TODO is to find a proper solution for this, maybe by implementing eglBindTexImage on
1976 // OSX?
1977 if (buftype != EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE)
1978 {
1979 return EglBadAttribute();
1980 }
1981 }
1982
1983 if (buftype == EGL_D3D_TEXTURE_2D_SHARE_HANDLE_ANGLE)
1984 {
1985 EGLint width = static_cast<EGLint>(attributes.get(EGL_WIDTH, 0));
1986 EGLint height = static_cast<EGLint>(attributes.get(EGL_HEIGHT, 0));
1987
1988 if (width == 0 || height == 0)
1989 {
1990 return EglBadAttribute();
1991 }
1992
1993 const Caps &caps = display->getCaps();
1994 if (textureFormat != EGL_NO_TEXTURE && !caps.textureNPOT &&
1995 (!gl::isPow2(width) || !gl::isPow2(height)))
1996 {
1997 return EglBadMatch();
1998 }
1999 }
2000
2001 if (buftype == EGL_IOSURFACE_ANGLE)
2002 {
2003 if (static_cast<EGLenum>(textureTarget) != config->bindToTextureTarget)
2004 {
2005 return EglBadAttribute()
2006 << "EGL_IOSURFACE requires the texture target to match the config";
2007 }
2008 if (textureFormat != EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA)
2009 {
2010 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_IOSURFACE requires the EGL_TEXTURE_RGBA format";
2011 }
2012
2013 if (!attributes.contains(EGL_WIDTH) || !attributes.contains(EGL_HEIGHT) ||
2014 !attributes.contains(EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT) ||
2015 !attributes.contains(EGL_TEXTURE_TYPE_ANGLE) ||
2016 !attributes.contains(EGL_TEXTURE_INTERNAL_FORMAT_ANGLE) ||
2017 !attributes.contains(EGL_IOSURFACE_PLANE_ANGLE))
2018 {
2019 return EglBadParameter() << "Missing required attribute for EGL_IOSURFACE";
2020 }
2021 }
2022
2023 ANGLE_TRY(display->validateClientBuffer(config, buftype, buffer, attributes));
2024
2025 return NoError();
2026}

2106
2107Error ValidateMakeCurrent(Display *display, Surface *draw, Surface *read, gl::Context *context)
2108{
2109 if (context == EGL_NO_CONTEXT && (draw != EGL_NO_SURFACE || read != EGL_NO_SURFACE))
2110 {
2111 return EglBadMatch() << "If ctx is EGL_NO_CONTEXT, surfaces must be EGL_NO_SURFACE";
2112 }
2113
2114 // If ctx is EGL_NO_CONTEXT and either draw or read are not EGL_NO_SURFACE, an EGL_BAD_MATCH
2115 // error is generated. EGL_KHR_surfaceless_context allows both surfaces to be EGL_NO_SURFACE.
2116 if (context != EGL_NO_CONTEXT && (draw == EGL_NO_SURFACE || read == EGL_NO_SURFACE))
2117 {
2118 if (display->getExtensions().surfacelessContext)
2119 {
2120 if ((draw == EGL_NO_SURFACE) != (read == EGL_NO_SURFACE))
2121 {
2122 return EglBadMatch() << "If ctx is not EGL_NOT_CONTEXT, draw or read must "
2123 "both be EGL_NO_SURFACE, or both not";
2124 }
2125 }
2126 else
2127 {
2128 return EglBadMatch()
2129 << "If ctx is not EGL_NO_CONTEXT, surfaces must not be EGL_NO_SURFACE";
2130 }
2131 }
2132
2133 // If either of draw or read is a valid surface and the other is EGL_NO_SURFACE, an
2134 // EGL_BAD_MATCH error is generated.
2135 if ((read == EGL_NO_SURFACE) != (draw == EGL_NO_SURFACE))
2136 {
2137 return EglBadMatch()
2138 << "read and draw must both be valid surfaces, or both be EGL_NO_SURFACE";
2139 }
2140
2141 if (display == EGL_NO_DISPLAY || !Display::isValidDisplay(display))
2142 {
2143 return EglBadDisplay() << "'dpy' not a valid EGLDisplay handle";
2144 }
2145
2146 // EGL 1.5 spec: dpy can be uninitialized if all other parameters are null
2147 if (!display->isInitialized() &&
2148 (context != EGL_NO_CONTEXT || draw != EGL_NO_SURFACE || read != EGL_NO_SURFACE))
2149 {
2150 return EglNotInitialized() << "'dpy' not initialized";
2151 }
2152
2153 if (context != EGL_NO_CONTEXT)
2154 {
2155 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
2156 }
2157
2158 if (display->isInitialized() && display->isDeviceLost())
2159 {
2160 return EglContextLost();
2161 }
2162
2163 if (draw != EGL_NO_SURFACE)
2164 {
2165 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSurface(display, draw));
2166 }
2167
2168 if (read != EGL_NO_SURFACE)
2169 {
2170 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSurface(display, read));
2171 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateCompatibleSurface(display, context, read));
2172 }
2173
2174 if (draw != read)
2175 {
2176 if (draw)
2177 {
2178 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateCompatibleSurface(display, context, draw));
2179 }
2180 if (read)
2181 {
2182 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateCompatibleSurface(display, context, read));
2183 }
2184 }
2185 return NoError();
2186}
2187
2188Error ValidateCompatibleSurface(const Display *display,
2189 gl::Context *context,
2190 const Surface *surface)
2191{
2192 const Config *contextConfig = context->getConfig();
2193 const Config *surfaceConfig = surface->getConfig();
2194
2195 // Surface compatible with client API - only OPENGL_ES supported
2196 switch (context->getClientMajorVersion())
2197 {
2198 case 1:
2199 if (!(surfaceConfig->renderableType & EGL_OPENGL_ES_BIT))
2200 {
2201 return EglBadMatch() << "Surface not compatible with OpenGL ES 1.x.";
2202 }
2203 break;
2204 case 2:
2205 if (!(surfaceConfig->renderableType & EGL_OPENGL_ES2_BIT))
2206 {
2207 return EglBadMatch() << "Surface not compatible with OpenGL ES 2.x.";
2208 }
2209 break;
2210 case 3:
2211 if (!(surfaceConfig->renderableType & (EGL_OPENGL_ES2_BIT | EGL_OPENGL_ES3_BIT)))
2212 {
2213 return EglBadMatch() << "Surface not compatible with OpenGL ES 3.x.";
2214 }
2215 break;
2216 default:
2217 return EglBadMatch() << "Surface not compatible with Context API.";
2218 }
2219
2220 // EGL KHR no config context
2221 if (context->getConfig() == EGL_NO_CONFIG_KHR)
2222 {
2223 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
2224 if (displayExtensions.noConfigContext)
2225 {
2226 return NoError();
2227 }
2228 return EglBadMatch() << "Context with no config is not supported.";
2229 }
2230
2231 if (!surface->flexibleSurfaceCompatibilityRequested())
2232 {
2233 // Config compatibility is defined in section 2.2 of the EGL 1.5 spec
2234
2235 bool colorBufferCompat = surfaceConfig->colorBufferType == contextConfig->colorBufferType;
2236 if (!colorBufferCompat)
2237 {
2238 return EglBadMatch() << "Color buffer types are not compatible.";
2239 }
2240
2241 bool colorCompat = surfaceConfig->redSize == contextConfig->redSize &&
2242 surfaceConfig->greenSize == contextConfig->greenSize &&
2243 surfaceConfig->blueSize == contextConfig->blueSize &&
2244 surfaceConfig->alphaSize == contextConfig->alphaSize &&
2245 surfaceConfig->luminanceSize == contextConfig->luminanceSize;
2246 if (!colorCompat)
2247 {
2248 return EglBadMatch() << "Color buffer sizes are not compatible.";
2249 }
2250
2251 bool componentTypeCompat =
2252 surfaceConfig->colorComponentType == contextConfig->colorComponentType;
2253 if (!componentTypeCompat)
2254 {
2255 return EglBadMatch() << "Color buffer component types are not compatible.";
2256 }
2257
2258 bool dsCompat = surfaceConfig->depthSize == contextConfig->depthSize &&
2259 surfaceConfig->stencilSize == contextConfig->stencilSize;
2260 if (!dsCompat)
2261 {
2262 return EglBadMatch() << "Depth-stencil buffer types are not compatible.";
2263 }
2264 }
2265
2266 bool surfaceTypeCompat = (surfaceConfig->surfaceType & contextConfig->surfaceType) != 0;
2267 if (!surfaceTypeCompat)
2268 {
2269 return EglBadMatch() << "Surface type is not compatible.";
2270 }
2271
2272 return NoError();
2273}
2274
2275Error ValidateCreateImage(const Display *display,
2276 gl::Context *context,
2277 EGLenum target,
2278 EGLClientBuffer buffer,
2279 const AttributeMap &attributes)
2280{
2281
2282 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
2283
2284 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
2285
2286 // TODO(geofflang): Complete validation from EGL_KHR_image_base:
2287 // If the resource specified by <dpy>, <ctx>, <target>, <buffer> and <attrib_list> is itself an
2288 // EGLImage sibling, the error EGL_BAD_ACCESS is generated.
2289
2290 for (AttributeMap::const_iterator attributeIter = attributes.begin();
2291 attributeIter != attributes.end(); attributeIter++)
2292 {
2293 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter->first;
2294 EGLAttrib value = attributeIter->second;
2295
2296 switch (attribute)
2297 {
2298 case EGL_IMAGE_PRESERVED:
2299 switch (value)
2300 {
2301 case EGL_TRUE:
2302 case EGL_FALSE:
2303 break;
2304
2305 default:
2306 return EglBadParameter()
2307 << "EGL_IMAGE_PRESERVED must be EGL_TRUE or EGL_FALSE.";
2308 }
2309 break;
2310
2311 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL:
2312 if (!displayExtensions.glTexture2DImage &&
2313 !displayExtensions.glTextureCubemapImage && !displayExtensions.glTexture3DImage)
2314 {
2315 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL cannot be used "
2316 "without KHR_gl_texture_*_image support.";
2317 }
2318
2319 if (value < 0)
2320 {
2321 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL cannot be negative.";
2322 }
2323 break;
2324
2325 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_ZOFFSET:
2326 if (!displayExtensions.glTexture3DImage)
2327 {
2328 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_GL_TEXTURE_ZOFFSET cannot be used "
2329 "without KHR_gl_texture_3D_image support.";
2330 }
2331 break;
2332
2333 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE:
2334 if (!displayExtensions.glColorspace)
2335 {
2336 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_GL_COLORSPACE cannot be used "
2337 "without EGL_KHR_gl_colorspace support.";
2338 }
2339 switch (value)
2340 {
2341 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE_DEFAULT_EXT:
2342 break;
2343 default:
2344 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateColorspaceAttribute(displayExtensions, value));
2345 break;
2346 }
2347 break;
2348
2349 case EGL_TEXTURE_INTERNAL_FORMAT_ANGLE:
2350 if (!displayExtensions.imageD3D11Texture)
2351 {
2352 return EglBadParameter()
2353 << "EGL_TEXTURE_INTERNAL_FORMAT_ANGLE and EGL_TEXTURE_TYPE_ANGLE cannot "
2354 "be used without EGL_ANGLE_image_d3d11_texture support.";
2355 }
2356 break;
2357
2358 case EGL_WIDTH:
2359 case EGL_HEIGHT:
2360 if (target != EGL_LINUX_DMA_BUF_EXT)
2361 {
2362 return EglBadParameter()
2363 << "Parameter cannot be used if target is not EGL_LINUX_DMA_BUF_EXT";
2364 }
2365 break;
2366
2367 case EGL_LINUX_DRM_FOURCC_EXT:
2368 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_FD_EXT:
2369 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_OFFSET_EXT:
2370 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_PITCH_EXT:
2371 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_FD_EXT:
2372 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_OFFSET_EXT:
2373 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_PITCH_EXT:
2374 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_FD_EXT:
2375 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_OFFSET_EXT:
2376 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_PITCH_EXT:
2377 if (!displayExtensions.imageDmaBufImportEXT)
2378 {
2379 return EglBadParameter() << "Parameter cannot be used without "
2380 "EGL_EXT_image_dma_buf_import support.";
2381 }
2382 break;
2383
2384 case EGL_YUV_COLOR_SPACE_HINT_EXT:
2385 if (!displayExtensions.imageDmaBufImportEXT)
2386 {
2387 return EglBadParameter() << "Parameter cannot be used without "
2388 "EGL_EXT_image_dma_buf_import support.";
2389 }
2390
2391 switch (value)
2392 {
2393 case EGL_ITU_REC601_EXT:
2394 case EGL_ITU_REC709_EXT:
2395 case EGL_ITU_REC2020_EXT:
2396 break;
2397
2398 default:
2399 return EglBadParameter()
2400 << "Invalid value for EGL_YUV_COLOR_SPACE_HINT_EXT.";
2401 }
2402 break;
2403
2404 case EGL_SAMPLE_RANGE_HINT_EXT:
2405 if (!displayExtensions.imageDmaBufImportEXT)
2406 {
2407 return EglBadParameter() << "Parameter cannot be used without "
2408 "EGL_EXT_image_dma_buf_import support.";
2409 }
2410
2411 switch (value)
2412 {
2413 case EGL_YUV_FULL_RANGE_EXT:
2414 case EGL_YUV_NARROW_RANGE_EXT:
2415 break;
2416
2417 default:
2418 return EglBadParameter() << "Invalid value for EGL_SAMPLE_RANGE_HINT_EXT.";
2419 }
2420 break;
2421
2422 case EGL_YUV_CHROMA_HORIZONTAL_SITING_HINT_EXT:
2423 case EGL_YUV_CHROMA_VERTICAL_SITING_HINT_EXT:
2424 if (!displayExtensions.imageDmaBufImportEXT)
2425 {
2426 return EglBadParameter() << "Parameter cannot be used without "
2427 "EGL_EXT_image_dma_buf_import support.";
2428 }
2429
2430 switch (value)
2431 {
2432 case EGL_YUV_CHROMA_SITING_0_EXT:
2433 case EGL_YUV_CHROMA_SITING_0_5_EXT:
2434 break;
2435
2436 default:
2437 return EglBadParameter()
2438 << "Invalid value for EGL_YUV_CHROMA_HORIZONTAL_SITING_HINT_EXT or "
2439 "EGL_YUV_CHROMA_VERTICAL_SITING_HINT_EXT.";
2440 }
2441 break;
2442
2443 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_MODIFIER_LO_EXT:
2444 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_MODIFIER_HI_EXT:
2445 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_MODIFIER_LO_EXT:
2446 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_MODIFIER_HI_EXT:
2447 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_MODIFIER_LO_EXT:
2448 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_MODIFIER_HI_EXT:
2449 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_FD_EXT:
2450 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_OFFSET_EXT:
2451 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_PITCH_EXT:
2452 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_MODIFIER_LO_EXT:
2453 case EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_MODIFIER_HI_EXT:
2454 if (!displayExtensions.imageDmaBufImportModifiersEXT)
2455 {
2456 return EglBadParameter() << "Parameter cannot be used without "
2457 "EGL_EXT_image_dma_buf_import_modifiers support.";
2458 }
2459 break;
2460
2461 default:
2462 return EglBadParameter()
2463 << "invalid attribute: 0x" << std::hex << std::uppercase << attribute;
2464 }
2465 }
2466
2467 switch (target)
2468 {
2469 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_2D:
2470 {
2471 if (!displayExtensions.glTexture2DImage)
2472 {
2473 return EglBadParameter() << "KHR_gl_texture_2D_image not supported.";
2474 }
2475
2476 if (buffer == 0)
2477 {
2478 return EglBadParameter() << "buffer cannot reference a 2D texture with the name 0.";
2479 }
2480
2481 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
2482 const gl::Texture *texture =
2483 context->getTexture({egl_gl::EGLClientBufferToGLObjectHandle(buffer)});
2484 if (texture == nullptr || texture->getType() != gl::TextureType::_2D)
2485 {
2486 return EglBadParameter() << "target is not a 2D texture.";
2487 }
2488
2489 if (texture->getBoundSurface() != nullptr)
2490 {
2491 return EglBadAccess() << "texture has a surface bound to it.";
2492 }
2493
2494 EGLAttrib level = attributes.get(EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL, 0);
2495 if (texture->getWidth(gl::TextureTarget::_2D, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0 ||
2496 texture->getHeight(gl::TextureTarget::_2D, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0)
2497 {
2498 return EglBadParameter()
2499 << "target 2D texture does not have a valid size at specified level.";
2500 }
2501
2502 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateCreateImageMipLevelCommon(context, texture, level));
2503 }
2504 break;
2505
2506 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X:
2507 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X:
2508 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y:
2509 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y:
2510 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z:
2511 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z:
2512 {
2513 if (!displayExtensions.glTextureCubemapImage)
2514 {
2515 return EglBadParameter() << "KHR_gl_texture_cubemap_image not supported.";
2516 }
2517
2518 if (buffer == 0)
2519 {
2520 return EglBadParameter()
2521 << "buffer cannot reference a cubemap texture with the name 0.";
2522 }
2523
2524 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
2525 const gl::Texture *texture =
2526 context->getTexture({egl_gl::EGLClientBufferToGLObjectHandle(buffer)});
2527 if (texture == nullptr || texture->getType() != gl::TextureType::CubeMap)
2528 {
2529 return EglBadParameter() << "target is not a cubemap texture.";
2530 }
2531
2532 if (texture->getBoundSurface() != nullptr)
2533 {
2534 return EglBadAccess() << "texture has a surface bound to it.";
2535 }
2536
2537 EGLAttrib level = attributes.get(EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL, 0);
2538 gl::TextureTarget cubeMapFace = egl_gl::EGLCubeMapTargetToCubeMapTarget(target);
2539 if (texture->getWidth(cubeMapFace, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0 ||
2540 texture->getHeight(cubeMapFace, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0)
2541 {
2542 return EglBadParameter() << "target cubemap texture does not have a valid "
2543 "size at specified level and face.";
2544 }
2545
2546 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateCreateImageMipLevelCommon(context, texture, level));
2547
2548 if (level == 0 && !texture->isMipmapComplete() &&
2549 CubeTextureHasUnspecifiedLevel0Face(texture))
2550 {
2551 return EglBadParameter() << "if level is zero and the texture is incomplete, "
2552 "it must have all of its faces specified at level "
2553 "zero.";
2554 }
2555 }
2556 break;
2557
2558 case EGL_GL_TEXTURE_3D:
2559 {
2560 if (!displayExtensions.glTexture3DImage)
2561 {
2562 return EglBadParameter() << "KHR_gl_texture_3D_image not supported.";
2563 }
2564
2565 if (buffer == 0)
2566 {
2567 return EglBadParameter() << "buffer cannot reference a 3D texture with the name 0.";
2568 }
2569
2570 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
2571 const gl::Texture *texture =
2572 context->getTexture({egl_gl::EGLClientBufferToGLObjectHandle(buffer)});
2573 if (texture == nullptr || texture->getType() != gl::TextureType::_3D)
2574 {
2575 return EglBadParameter() << "target is not a 3D texture.";
2576 }
2577
2578 if (texture->getBoundSurface() != nullptr)
2579 {
2580 return EglBadAccess() << "texture has a surface bound to it.";
2581 }
2582
2583 EGLAttrib level = attributes.get(EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL, 0);
2584 EGLAttrib zOffset = attributes.get(EGL_GL_TEXTURE_ZOFFSET, 0);
2585 if (texture->getWidth(gl::TextureTarget::_3D, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0 ||
2586 texture->getHeight(gl::TextureTarget::_3D, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0 ||
2587 texture->getDepth(gl::TextureTarget::_3D, static_cast<size_t>(level)) == 0)
2588 {
2589 return EglBadParameter()
2590 << "target 3D texture does not have a valid size at specified level.";
2591 }
2592
2593 if (static_cast<size_t>(zOffset) >=
2594 texture->getDepth(gl::TextureTarget::_3D, static_cast<size_t>(level)))
2595 {
2596 return EglBadParameter() << "target 3D texture does not have enough layers "
2597 "for the specified Z offset at the specified "
2598 "level.";
2599 }
2600
2601 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateCreateImageMipLevelCommon(context, texture, level));
2602 }
2603 break;
2604
2605 case EGL_GL_RENDERBUFFER:
2606 {
2607 if (!displayExtensions.glRenderbufferImage)
2608 {
2609 return EglBadParameter() << "KHR_gl_renderbuffer_image not supported.";
2610 }
2611
2612 if (attributes.contains(EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL))
2613 {
2614 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_GL_TEXTURE_LEVEL cannot be used in "
2615 "conjunction with a renderbuffer target.";
2616 }
2617
2618 if (buffer == 0)
2619 {
2620 return EglBadParameter()
2621 << "buffer cannot reference a renderbuffer with the name 0.";
2622 }
2623
2624 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
2625 const gl::Renderbuffer *renderbuffer =
2626 context->getRenderbuffer({egl_gl::EGLClientBufferToGLObjectHandle(buffer)});
2627 if (renderbuffer == nullptr)
2628 {
2629 return EglBadParameter() << "target is not a renderbuffer.";
2630 }
2631
2632 if (renderbuffer->getSamples() > 0)
2633 {
2634 return EglBadParameter() << "target renderbuffer cannot be multisampled.";
2635 }
2636 }
2637 break;
2638
2639 case EGL_NATIVE_BUFFER_ANDROID:
2640 {
2641 if (!displayExtensions.imageNativeBuffer)
2642 {
2643 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_ANDROID_image_native_buffer not supported.";
2644 }
2645
2646 if (context != nullptr)
2647 {
2648 return EglBadContext() << "ctx must be EGL_NO_CONTEXT.";
2649 }
2650
2651 ANGLE_TRY(display->validateImageClientBuffer(context, target, buffer, attributes));
2652 }
2653 break;
2654
2655 case EGL_D3D11_TEXTURE_ANGLE:
2656 if (!displayExtensions.imageD3D11Texture)
2657 {
2658 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_ANGLE_image_d3d11_texture not supported.";
2659 }
2660
2661 if (context != nullptr)
2662 {
2663 return EglBadContext() << "ctx must be EGL_NO_CONTEXT.";
2664 }
2665
2666 ANGLE_TRY(display->validateImageClientBuffer(context, target, buffer, attributes));
2667 break;
2668
2669 case EGL_LINUX_DMA_BUF_EXT:
2670 if (!displayExtensions.imageDmaBufImportEXT)
2671 {
2672 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_EXT_image_dma_buf_import not supported.";
2673 }
2674
2675 if (context != nullptr)
2676 {
2677 return EglBadContext() << "ctx must be EGL_NO_CONTEXT.";
2678 }
2679
2680 if (buffer != nullptr)
2681 {
2682 return EglBadParameter() << "buffer must be NULL.";
2683 }
2684
2685 {
2686 EGLenum kRequiredParameters[] = {EGL_WIDTH,
2687 EGL_HEIGHT,
2688 EGL_LINUX_DRM_FOURCC_EXT,
2689 EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_FD_EXT,
2690 EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_OFFSET_EXT,
2691 EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_PITCH_EXT};
2692 for (EGLenum requiredParameter : kRequiredParameters)
2693 {
2694 if (!attributes.contains(requiredParameter))
2695 {
2696 return EglBadParameter()
2697 << "Missing required parameter " << gl::FmtHex(requiredParameter)
2698 << " for image target EGL_LINUX_DMA_BUF_EXT.";
2699 }
2700 }
2701
2702 bool containPlane0ModifierLo =
2703 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_MODIFIER_LO_EXT);
2704 bool containPlane0ModifierHi =
2705 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE0_MODIFIER_HI_EXT);
2706 bool containPlane1ModifierLo =
2707 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_MODIFIER_LO_EXT);
2708 bool containPlane1ModifierHi =
2709 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE1_MODIFIER_HI_EXT);
2710 bool containPlane2ModifierLo =
2711 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_MODIFIER_LO_EXT);
2712 bool containPlane2ModifierHi =
2713 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE2_MODIFIER_HI_EXT);
2714 bool containPlane3ModifierLo =
2715 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_MODIFIER_LO_EXT);
2716 bool containPlane3ModifierHi =
2717 attributes.contains(EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE3_MODIFIER_HI_EXT);
2718 if ((containPlane0ModifierLo ^ containPlane0ModifierHi) ||
2719 (containPlane1ModifierLo ^ containPlane1ModifierHi) ||
2720 (containPlane2ModifierLo ^ containPlane2ModifierHi) ||
2721 (containPlane3ModifierLo ^ containPlane3ModifierHi))
2722 {
2723 return EglBadParameter()
2724 << "the list of attributes contains EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE*_MODIFIER_LO_EXT "
2725 "but not EGL_DMA_BUF_PLANE*_MODIFIER_HI_EXT or vice versa.";
2726 }
2727 }
2728 break;
2729
2730 case EGL_METAL_TEXTURE_ANGLE:
2731 if (!displayExtensions.mtlTextureClientBuffer)
2732 {
2733 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_ANGLE_metal_texture_client_buffer not supported.";
2734 }
2735
2736 if (context != nullptr)
2737 {
2738 return EglBadContext() << "ctx must be EGL_NO_CONTEXT.";
2739 }
2740
2741 ANGLE_TRY(display->validateImageClientBuffer(context, target, buffer, attributes));
2742 break;
2743
2744 default:
2745 return EglBadParameter()
2746 << "invalid target: 0x" << std::hex << std::uppercase << target;
2747 }
2748
2749 if (attributes.contains(EGL_GL_TEXTURE_ZOFFSET) && target != EGL_GL_TEXTURE_3D)
2750 {
2751 return EglBadParameter() << "EGL_GL_TEXTURE_ZOFFSET must be used with a 3D texture target.";
2752 }
2753
2754 return NoError();
2755}

2759 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateImage(display, image));
2760
2761 return NoError();

2764Error ValidateCreateImageKHR(const Display *display,
2765 gl::Context *context,
2766 EGLenum target,
2767 EGLClientBuffer buffer,
2768 const AttributeMap &attributes)
2769{
2770 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
2771
2772 if (!display->getExtensions().imageBase && !display->getExtensions().image)
2773 {
2774 // It is out of spec what happens when calling an extension function when the extension is
2775 // not available.
2776 // EGL_BAD_DISPLAY seems like a reasonable error.
2777 return EglBadDisplay() << "EGL_KHR_image not supported.";
2778 }
2779
2780 return ValidateCreateImage(display, context, target, buffer, attributes);
2781}

2784{

2786
2787 if (!display->getExtensions().imageBase && !display->getExtensions().image)
2788 {
2789 // It is out of spec what happens when calling an extension function when the extension is
2790 // not available.
2791 // EGL_BAD_DISPLAY seems like a reasonable error.
2792 return EglBadDisplay();
2793 }
2794
2795 return NoError();
2796}

2798Error ValidateCreateDeviceANGLE(EGLint device_type,
2799 void *native_device,
2800 const EGLAttrib *attrib_list)
2801{
2802 const ClientExtensions &clientExtensions = Display::GetClientExtensions();
2803 if (!clientExtensions.deviceCreation)
2804 {
2805 return EglBadAccess() << "Device creation extension not active";
2806 }
2807
2808 if (attrib_list != nullptr && attrib_list[0] != EGL_NONE)
2809 {
2810 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid attrib_list parameter";
2811 }
2812
2813 switch (device_type)
2814 {
2815 case EGL_D3D11_DEVICE_ANGLE:
2816 if (!clientExtensions.deviceCreationD3D11)
2817 {
2818 return EglBadAttribute() << "D3D11 device creation extension not active";
2819 }
2820 break;
2821 default:
2822 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid device_type parameter";
2823 }
2824
2825 return NoError();
2826}

2828Error ValidateReleaseDeviceANGLE(Device *device)
2829{
2830 const ClientExtensions &clientExtensions = Display::GetClientExtensions();
2831 if (!clientExtensions.deviceCreation)
2832 {
2833 return EglBadAccess() << "Device creation extension not active";
2834 }
2835
2836 if (device == EGL_NO_DEVICE_EXT || !Device::IsValidDevice(device))
2837 {
2838 return EglBadDevice() << "Invalid device parameter";
2839 }
2840
2841 Display *owningDisplay = device->getOwningDisplay();
2842 if (owningDisplay != nullptr)
2843 {
2844 return EglBadDevice() << "Device must have been created using eglCreateDevice";
2845 }
2846
2847 return NoError();
2848}
2849
2850Error ValidateCreateSyncBase(const Display *display,
2851 EGLenum type,
2852 const AttributeMap &attribs,
2853 const Display *currentDisplay,
2854 const gl::Context *currentContext,
2855 bool isExt)
2856{
2857 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
2858
2859 switch (type)
2860 {
2861 case EGL_SYNC_FENCE_KHR:
2862 if (!attribs.isEmpty())
2863 {
2864 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid attribute";
2865 }
2866
2867 if (!display->getExtensions().fenceSync)
2868 {
2869 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_KHR_fence_sync extension is not available";
2870 }
2871
2872 if (display != currentDisplay)
2873 {
2874 return EglBadMatch() << "CreateSync can only be called on the current display";
2875 }
2876
2877 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(currentDisplay, currentContext));
2878
2879 if (!currentContext->getExtensions().eglSyncOES)
2880 {
2881 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_SYNC_FENCE_KHR cannot be used without "
2882 "GL_OES_EGL_sync support.";
2883 }
2884 break;
2885
2886 case EGL_SYNC_NATIVE_FENCE_ANDROID:
2887 if (!display->getExtensions().fenceSync)
2888 {
2889 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_KHR_fence_sync extension is not available";
2890 }
2891
2892 if (!display->getExtensions().nativeFenceSyncANDROID)
2893 {
2894 return EglBadDisplay()
2895 << "EGL_ANDROID_native_fence_sync extension is not available.";
2896 }
2897
2898 if (display != currentDisplay)
2899 {
2900 return EglBadMatch() << "CreateSync can only be called on the current display";
2901 }
2902
2903 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(currentDisplay, currentContext));
2904
2905 if (!currentContext->getExtensions().eglSyncOES)
2906 {
2907 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_SYNC_FENCE_KHR cannot be used without "
2908 "GL_OES_EGL_sync support.";
2909 }
2910
2911 for (const auto &attributeIter : attribs)
2912 {
2913 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter.first;
2914
2915 switch (attribute)
2916 {
2917 case EGL_SYNC_NATIVE_FENCE_FD_ANDROID:
2918 break;
2919
2920 default:
2921 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid attribute";
2922 }
2923 }
2924 break;
2925
2926 case EGL_SYNC_REUSABLE_KHR:
2927 if (!attribs.isEmpty())
2928 {
2929 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid attribute";
2930 }
2931
2932 if (!display->getExtensions().reusableSyncKHR)
2933 {
2934 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_KHR_reusable_sync extension is not available.";
2935 }
2936 break;
2937
2938 default:
2939 if (isExt)
2940 {
2941 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid type parameter";
2942 }

3288Error ValidateStreamConsumerGLTextureExternalAttribsNV(const Display *display,
3289 gl::Context *context,
3290 const Stream *stream,
3291 const AttributeMap &attribs)
3292{
3293 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
3294
3295 const DisplayExtensions &displayExtensions = display->getExtensions();
3296 if (!displayExtensions.streamConsumerGLTexture)
3297 {
3298 return EglBadAccess() << "Stream consumer extension not active";
3299 }
3300
3301 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateContext(display, context));
3302
3303 // Although technically not a requirement in spec, the context needs to be checked for support
3304 // for external textures or future logic will cause assertations. This extension is also
3305 // effectively useless without external textures.
3306 if (!context->getExtensions().eglStreamConsumerExternalNV)
3307 {
3308 return EglBadAccess() << "EGL stream consumer external GL extension not enabled";
3309 }
3310
3311 if (stream == EGL_NO_STREAM_KHR || !display->isValidStream(stream))
3312 {
3313 return EglBadStream() << "Invalid stream";
3314 }
3315
3316 if (stream->getState() != EGL_STREAM_STATE_CREATED_KHR)
3317 {
3318 return EglBadState() << "Invalid stream state";
3319 }
3320
3321 const gl::Caps &glCaps = context->getCaps();
3322
3323 EGLAttrib colorBufferType = EGL_RGB_BUFFER;
3324 EGLAttrib planeCount = -1;
3325 EGLAttrib plane[3];
3326 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
3327 {
3328 plane[i] = -1;
3329 }
3330 for (const auto &attributeIter : attribs)
3331 {
3332 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter.first;
3333 EGLAttrib value = attributeIter.second;
3334
3335 switch (attribute)
3336 {
3337 case EGL_COLOR_BUFFER_TYPE:
3338 if (value != EGL_RGB_BUFFER && value != EGL_YUV_BUFFER_EXT)
3339 {
3340 return EglBadParameter() << "Invalid color buffer type";
3341 }
3342 colorBufferType = value;
3343 break;
3344 case EGL_YUV_NUMBER_OF_PLANES_EXT:
3345 // planeCount = -1 is a tag for the default plane count so the value must be checked
3346 // to be positive here to ensure future logic doesn't break on invalid negative
3347 // inputs
3348 if (value < 0)
3349 {
3350 return EglBadMatch() << "Invalid plane count";
3351 }
3352 planeCount = value;
3353 break;
3354 default:
3355 if (attribute >= EGL_YUV_PLANE0_TEXTURE_UNIT_NV &&
3356 attribute <= EGL_YUV_PLANE2_TEXTURE_UNIT_NV)
3357 {
3358 if ((value < 0 ||
3359 value >= static_cast<EGLAttrib>(glCaps.maxCombinedTextureImageUnits)) &&
3360 value != EGL_NONE)
3361 {
3362 return EglBadAccess() << "Invalid texture unit";
3363 }
3364 plane[attribute - EGL_YUV_PLANE0_TEXTURE_UNIT_NV] = value;
3365 }
3366 else
3367 {
3368 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid attribute";
3369 }
3370 }
3371 }
3372
3373 if (colorBufferType == EGL_RGB_BUFFER)
3374 {
3375 if (planeCount > 0)
3376 {
3377 return EglBadMatch() << "Plane count must be 0 for RGB buffer";
3378 }
3379 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
3380 {
3381 if (plane[i] != -1)
3382 {
3383 return EglBadMatch() << "Planes cannot be specified";
3384 }
3385 }
3386
3387 // Lookup the texture and ensure it is correct
3388 gl::Texture *texture = context->getState().getTargetTexture(gl::TextureType::External);
3389 if (texture == nullptr || texture->id().value == 0)
3390 {
3391 return EglBadAccess() << "No external texture bound";
3392 }
3393 }
3394 else
3395 {
3396 if (planeCount == -1)
3397 {
3398 planeCount = 2;
3399 }
3400 if (planeCount < 1 || planeCount > 3)
3401 {
3402 return EglBadMatch() << "Invalid YUV plane count";
3403 }
3404 for (EGLAttrib i = planeCount; i < 3; i++)
3405 {
3406 if (plane[i] != -1)
3407 {
3408 return EglBadMatch() << "Invalid plane specified";
3409 }
3410 }
3411
3412 // Set to ensure no texture is referenced more than once
3413 std::set<gl::Texture *> textureSet;
3414 for (EGLAttrib i = 0; i < planeCount; i++)
3415 {
3416 if (plane[i] == -1)
3417 {
3418 return EglBadMatch() << "Not all planes specified";
3419 }
3420 if (plane[i] != EGL_NONE)
3421 {
3422 gl::Texture *texture = context->getState().getSamplerTexture(
3423 static_cast<unsigned int>(plane[i]), gl::TextureType::External);
3424 if (texture == nullptr || texture->id().value == 0)
3425 {
3426 return EglBadAccess()
3427 << "No external texture bound at one or more specified texture units";
3428 }
3429 if (textureSet.find(texture) != textureSet.end())
3430 {
3431 return EglBadAccess() << "Multiple planes bound to same texture object";
3432 }
3433 textureSet.insert(texture);
3434 }
3435 }
3436 }
3437
3438 return NoError();
3439}
