3731 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSurface(display, surface));
3732
3733 if (buffer != EGL_BACK_BUFFER)
3734 {
3735 return EglBadParameter();
3736 }
3737
3738 if (eglSurface == EGL_NO_SURFACE || surface->getType() == EGL_WINDOW_BIT)
3739 {
3740 return EglBadSurface();
3741 }
3742
3743 if (surface->getBoundTexture())
3744 {
3745 return EglBadAccess();
3746 }
3747
3748 if (surface->getTextureFormat() == TextureFormat::NoTexture)
3749 {
3750 return EglBadMatch();
3751 }
3752
3753 if (context)
3754 {
3755 gl::TextureType type = egl_gl::EGLTextureTargetToTextureType(surface->getTextureTarget());
3756 *textureObject = context->getTextureByType(type);
3757 ASSERT(*textureObject != nullptr);
3758
3759 if ((*textureObject)->getImmutableFormat())
3760 {
3761 return EglBadMatch();
3762 }
3763 }
3764
3765 return NoError();
3766}

3964Error ValidateProgramCacheQueryANGLE(const Display *display,
3965 EGLint index,
3966 void *key,
3967 EGLint *keysize,
3968 void *binary,
3969 EGLint *binarysize)
3970{
3971 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
3972
3973 if (!display->getExtensions().programCacheControl)
3974 {
3975 return EglBadAccess() << "Extension not supported";
3976 }
3977
3978 if (index < 0 || index >= display->programCacheGetAttrib(EGL_PROGRAM_CACHE_SIZE_ANGLE))
3979 {
3980 return EglBadParameter() << "Program index out of range.";
3981 }
3982
3983 if (keysize == nullptr || binarysize == nullptr)
3984 {
3985 return EglBadParameter() << "keysize and binarysize must always be valid pointers.";
3986 }
3987
3988 if (binary && *keysize != static_cast<EGLint>(egl::BlobCache::kKeyLength))
3989 {
3990 return EglBadParameter() << "Invalid program key size.";
3991 }
3992
3993 if ((key == nullptr) != (binary == nullptr))
3994 {
3995 return EglBadParameter() << "key and binary must both be null or both non-null.";
3996 }
3997
3998 return NoError();
3999}

4060Error ValidateSurfaceAttrib(const Display *display,
4061 const Surface *surface,
4062 EGLint attribute,
4063 EGLint value)
4064{
4065 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
4066 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSurface(display, surface));
4067
4068 if (surface == EGL_NO_SURFACE)
4069 {
4070 return EglBadSurface() << "Surface cannot be EGL_NO_SURFACE.";
4071 }
4072
4073 switch (attribute)
4074 {
4075 case EGL_MIPMAP_LEVEL:
4076 break;
4077
4078 case EGL_MULTISAMPLE_RESOLVE:
4079 switch (value)
4080 {
4081 case EGL_MULTISAMPLE_RESOLVE_DEFAULT:
4082 break;
4083
4084 case EGL_MULTISAMPLE_RESOLVE_BOX:
4085 if ((surface->getConfig()->surfaceType & EGL_MULTISAMPLE_RESOLVE_BOX_BIT) == 0)
4086 {
4087 return EglBadMatch()
4088 << "Surface does not support EGL_MULTISAMPLE_RESOLVE_BOX.";
4089 }
4090 break;
4091
4092 default:
4093 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid multisample resolve type.";
4094 }
4095 break;
4096
4097 case EGL_SWAP_BEHAVIOR:
4098 switch (value)
4099 {
4100 case EGL_BUFFER_PRESERVED:
4101 if ((surface->getConfig()->surfaceType & EGL_SWAP_BEHAVIOR_PRESERVED_BIT) == 0)
4102 {
4103 return EglBadMatch()
4104 << "Surface does not support EGL_SWAP_BEHAVIOR_PRESERVED.";
4105 }
4106 break;
4107
4108 case EGL_BUFFER_DESTROYED:
4109 break;
4110
4111 default:
4112 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid swap behaviour.";
4113 }
4114 break;
4115
4116 case EGL_WIDTH:
4117 case EGL_HEIGHT:
4118 if (!display->getExtensions().windowFixedSize)
4119 {
4120 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_WIDTH or EGL_HEIGHT cannot be set without "
4121 "EGL_ANGLE_window_fixed_size support.";
4122 }
4123 if (!surface->isFixedSize())
4124 {
4125 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_WIDTH or EGL_HEIGHT cannot be set without "
4126 "EGL_FIXED_SIZE_ANGLE being enabled on the surface.";
4127 }
4128 break;
4129
4130 case EGL_TIMESTAMPS_ANDROID:
4131 if (!display->getExtensions().getFrameTimestamps)
4132 {
4133 return EglBadAttribute() << "EGL_TIMESTAMPS_ANDROID cannot be used without "
4134 "EGL_ANDROID_get_frame_timestamps support.";
4135 }
4136 switch (value)
4137 {
4138 case EGL_TRUE:
4139 case EGL_FALSE:
4140 break;
4141
4142 default:
4143 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid value.";
4144 }
4145 break;
4146
4147 default:
4148 return EglBadAttribute() << "Invalid surface attribute.";
4149 }
4150
4151 return NoError();
4152}

4520Error ValidateQueryStringiANGLE(const Display *display, EGLint name, EGLint index)
4521{

4527 }

4537 case EGL_FEATURE_CATEGORY_ANGLE:

4539 case EGL_FEATURE_BUG_ANGLE:

4548 {

4607
4608Error ValidateCreateNativeClientBufferANDROID(const egl::AttributeMap &attribMap)
4609{
4610 int width = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_WIDTH, 0);
4611 int height = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_HEIGHT, 0);
4612 int redSize = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_RED_SIZE, 0);
4613 int greenSize = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_GREEN_SIZE, 0);
4614 int blueSize = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_BLUE_SIZE, 0);
4615 int alphaSize = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_ALPHA_SIZE, 0);
4616 int usage = attribMap.getAsInt(EGL_NATIVE_BUFFER_USAGE_ANDROID, 0);
4617
4618 for (AttributeMap::const_iterator attributeIter = attribMap.begin();
4619 attributeIter != attribMap.end(); attributeIter++)
4620 {
4621 EGLAttrib attribute = attributeIter->first;
4622 switch (attribute)
4623 {
4624 case EGL_WIDTH:
4625 case EGL_HEIGHT:
4626 // Validation done after the switch statement
4627 break;
4628 case EGL_RED_SIZE:
4629 case EGL_GREEN_SIZE:
4630 case EGL_BLUE_SIZE:
4631 case EGL_ALPHA_SIZE:
4632 if (redSize < 0 || greenSize < 0 || blueSize < 0 || alphaSize < 0)
4633 {
4634 return EglBadParameter() << "incorrect channel size requested";
4635 }
4636 break;
4637 case EGL_NATIVE_BUFFER_USAGE_ANDROID:
4638 // The buffer must be used for either a texture or a renderbuffer.
4639 if ((usage & ~(EGL_NATIVE_BUFFER_USAGE_PROTECTED_BIT_ANDROID |
4640 EGL_NATIVE_BUFFER_USAGE_RENDERBUFFER_BIT_ANDROID |
4641 EGL_NATIVE_BUFFER_USAGE_TEXTURE_BIT_ANDROID)) != 0)
4642 {
4643 return EglBadParameter() << "invalid usage flag";
4644 }
4645 break;
4646 case EGL_NONE:
4647 break;
4648 default:
4649 return EglBadAttribute() << "invalid attribute";
4650 }
4651 }
4652
4653 // Validate EGL_WIDTH and EGL_HEIGHT values passed in. Done here to account
4654 // for the case where EGL_WIDTH and EGL_HEIGHT were not part of the attribute list.
4655 if (width <= 0 || height <= 0)
4656 {
4657 return EglBadParameter() << "incorrect buffer dimensions requested";
4658 }
4659
4660 if (gl::GetAndroidHardwareBufferFormatFromChannelSizes(attribMap) == 0)
4661 {
4662 return EglBadParameter() << "unsupported format";
4663 }
4664 return NoError();
4665}

4697Error ValidateSignalSyncKHR(const Display *display, const Sync *sync, EGLint mode)
4698{
4699 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateDisplay(display));
4700
4701 ANGLE_TRY(ValidateSync(display, sync));
4702
4703 if (sync->getType() == EGL_SYNC_REUSABLE_KHR)
4704 {
4705 if (!display->getExtensions().reusableSyncKHR)
4706 {
4707 return EglBadMatch() << "EGL_KHR_reusable_sync extension is not available.";
4708 }
4709
4710 if ((mode != EGL_SIGNALED_KHR) && (mode != EGL_UNSIGNALED_KHR))
4711 {
4712 return EglBadParameter() << "eglSignalSyncKHR invalid mode.";
4713 }
4714
4715 return NoError();
4716 }
4717
4718 return EglBadMatch();
4719}
